The article discusses the progress made since the G-20 Pittsburgh Summit in restoring growth and jobs and building a stronger global financial system. The G-20 leaders agreed to prioritize safeguarding and strengthening the recovery and laying the foundation for sustainable and balanced growth. They pledged to support existing recovery plans and calibrate fiscal consolidation to protect the recovery. The article highlights the achievements in strengthening the recovery, such as the US economy growing at close to 3% and the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act boosting GDP and employment. It also mentions the efforts to repair and reform the global financial system, including stress tests, financial reforms, and regulatory oversight. The article further discusses the modernization of international economic cooperation, increasing the voice of developing and transition countries, and launching initiatives for SME finance, global agriculture, and fighting corruption.